## Summary by Sourcery Update Upsonic to version 0.34.3. New Features: - Print the user name after the welcome message. Bug Fixes: - Resolve `TypeError` for `list[any]` and `list[int]`. - Fix list typing issues. Enhancements: - Add current datetime in tester mode. - Add comments inside the `dump_module` function. - Add user name print logging after the welcome message. - Add type annotations to functions. - Add print mechanism for exceptions on dump operations. Tests: - Add a try-except block for the get_username function.

## Reviewer's Guide by Sourcery This PR bumps the version of upsonic from 0.28.4 to 0.34.3, introducing several new features, bug fixes, and documentation improvements. The changes primarily involve updating the `requirements.txt` file to reflect the new version and removing now-redundant package specifications from `requirements.in`. #### Sequence diagram for enhanced user welcome flow ```mermaid sequenceDiagram actor User participant Client as Upsonic Client participant System as System User->>Client: Initialize client Client->>Client: print_welcome_message() Client->>System: get_username() alt Username retrieved successfully System-->>Client: return username Client->>User: Display welcome with username else Username retrieval fails System-->>Client: raise exception Client->>User: Display welcome without username end ``` #### Class diagram showing Upsonic client changes ```mermaid classDiagram class UpsonicClient { +dump_module() +get_username() +list[any] operations +list[int] operations +print_welcome_message() } note for UpsonicClient "Added type hints and improved error handling" ``` ### File-Level Changes | Change | Details | Files | | ------ | ------- | ----- | | Updated upsonic dependency |
  • Bumped upsonic version from 0.28.4 to 0.34.3.
| `requirements.txt` | | Removed now-redundant direct dependencies |
  • Removed direct specifications for packages now installed transitively via upsonic.
  • Removed pyperclip, google, duckduckgo-search, beautifulsoup4, pytesseract, pywifi-controls, and pynput from requirements.in.
| `requirements.in`
`requirements.txt` | | Added new dependencies |
  • Added beautifulsoup4, curl-cffi, duckduckgo-search, evdev, google, orjson, pexpect, pillow, ptyprocess, pynput, pytesseract, python-xlib, python3-xlib, pywifi-controls, soupsieve, and termcolor as dependencies.
| `requirements.txt` | | Updated existing dependencies |
  • Updated cryptography from 41.0.3 to 40.0.2.
  • Updated pyqt5-qt5 from 5.15.2 to 5.15.16.
  • Removed dependency on pyreadline3.
  • Removed dependency on pywin32.
| `requirements.txt` | | Removed unnecessary comments |
  • Removed comments related to default tools and unsafe packages in requirements.txt.
| `requirements.txt` | | Updated transitive dependencies |
  • Updated transitive dependencies as needed by the new upsonic version and other changes.
| `requirements.txt` | ---
